This paper deals with a security issue in software repositories, specifically typosquatting, which is a common problem in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a tool for identifying and reporting potentially erroneous imports to developers, which involves software engineering techniques (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The tool also uses a model of lexical similarity and package popularity, which could fall under the category of information retrieval or machine learning (cs.SI, cs.LG).
